thread.title: CAMP PENDLETON: Marine found dead with gunshot wound to head
thread.title_full: CAMP PENDLETON: Marine found dead with gunshot wound to head - Press Enterprise

author: LOUIS CASIANO JR.
title: CAMP PENDLETON: Marine found dead with gunshot wound to head
text:
By LOUIS CASIANO JR. / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 5, 2015 Updated: 11:10 p.m. A Marine was found dead Monday morning at a Camp Pendleton shooting range, base officials said.
The Marine, who was assigned to the 1st Marine Division, was found at 6 a.m. at Marksmanship Training Range 214 with a gunshot wound to the head, said division public affairs officer Lt. Colleen McFadden.
The Camp Pendleton Federal Fire Department responded to the scene. It was unclear Monday how the Marine was shot. The name and circumstances of the Marine’s death were not released.
An investigation has been launched.
“Our priority is to take care of the Marine’s family and friends in the unit,” McFadden said.�
